<h1> VWTEST </h1>


<h2> INSTALLATION INSTRUCCTIONS </h2>

There are none specific installation instructions, here is what i did:

1) /etc/hosts

  127.0.0.1       localhost vwtest.example.com

2) httpd-vhosts.conf

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerAdmin webmaster@dummy-host.example.com
    DocumentRoot "/var/www/vwtest/vwtest/"
    ServerName vwtest.example.com
    ServerAlias vwtest.example.com
    ErrorLog "/private/var/log/apache2/vwtest.example.com.err"
    CustomLog "/private/var/log/apache2/vwtest.example.com.log" common

    <Directory />
        Options FollowSymLinks
        AllowOverride All
        Order allow,deny
        Allow from all
        DirectoryIndex index.php index.html
   </Directory>
</VirtualHost>

3) If the 'Application runtime path "........./protected/runtime"' error appears, just grant 777 to that directory

mkdir -p /....DIR.....protected/runtime
chmod  -R 777 /....DIR....../protected/runtime

<h2> Access INFO </h2>

There are 3 methods on the API:

1) Generic API

http://vwtest.example.com/index.php/vw/api


2) ping

http://vwtest.example.com/index.php/vw/ping

3) Reserve

http://vwtest.example.com/index.php/vw/reverse
